## Remove file from local+remote

$ git rm notes/howto-homebrew.sh
$ git commit -m "..."
$ git push origin main

## ----------------------------------------------------------------- ##

$ git push origin localbranch:newremotebranch
$ git push origin -u existingremotebranch

## ----------------------------------------------------------------- ##

### Delete branch locally and remotely:

# delete the local branch
$ git branch -d localBranchName

# delete the remote branch
$ git push origin --delete remoteBranchName
# or
$ git push origin :remoteBranchName

If you get the error below, it may mean that someone else has already deleted the branch.
error: unable to push to unqualified destination: remoteBranchName The destination refspec neither matches an existing ref on the remote nor begins with refs/, and we are unable to guess a prefix based on the source ref. error: failed to push some refs to 'git@repository_name'
Try to synchronize your branch list using:

$ git fetch -p

The -p flag means "prune". After fetching, branches which no longer exist on the remote will be deleted.

## ----------------------------------------------------------------- ##

### PUSH ERROR: file > 100 MB

# error message
$ remote: error: GH001: Large files detected. You may want to try Git Large File Storage - https://git-lfs.github.com

# SOLUTION:
# https://git-lfs.github.com/
# - Download package dans /Applications
# - cd /Applications/git-lfs-darwin-amd64-v2.13.2/
$ ./install.sh

# - in each git repo where you will have big files (> 100 MB):
$ git lfs track “*.psd”
$ git add .gitattributes

## ----------------------------------------------------------------- ##

# ANNULER TOUS LES COMMITS NON PUSHES :
# https://makina-corpus.com/blog/metier/archives/git-annuler-proprement-un-commit-apres-un-push
# https://www.git-tower.com/learn/git/faq/undo-last-commit/
$ git reset --hard origin/HEAD

